#!/usr/bin/env O
# STEP-4: first-class coordination primitives.
#
# A Group makes the EXECUTION TOPOLOGY of several computations explicit in
# the value model. Where a Request names a single deferred computation, a
# Group names a collection of them together with a mode that says HOW they
# relate:
#
#   batch(a, b, ...)  — run all members; collect every outcome including failures
#                       (failures are wrapped as OError values, not propagated)
#   all(a, b, ...)    — all must succeed; any failure aborts the whole group
#   any(a, b, ...)    — redundancy/fallback; yields the first member to succeed
#   race(a, b, ...)   — latency competition; yields the first result to settle
#                       (NOTE: does not yet cancel losing work)
#
# A Group performs no work on its own. It is forced by `now(group)`, by
# `autonomous(group)`, or at document end under Autonomous policy.
#
# IMPORTANT: batch/all/any/race are SPECIAL FORMS. Under eager evaluation, their
# arguments are captured lazily. Under autonomous evaluation, Autonomous policy
# is preserved so captured request chains are also buffered for the scheduler.
# This means:
#
#   batch(realise(instantiate($e1)), realise(instantiate($e2)))
#
# always captures Request chains, never pre-resolved values. You do NOT need
# to wrap in lazy(...) to get meaningful group coordination - the group
# constructor handles deferral automatically.

# ── Group over plain values (runs without Nix) ───────────────────────────────
# nix_expr^ produces a NixExpr value WITHOUT invoking Nix, so this section is
# self-contained: it shows the topology over already-constructed values.
let e1 = nix_expr^( pkgs.hello )_nix_expr
let e2 = nix_expr^( pkgs.cowsay )_nix_expr
let e3 = nix_expr^( pkgs.figlet )_nix_expr

# batch(...) bundles the three expressions into one Group value.
let bundle = batch($e1, $e2, $e3)

# now(group) forces the group per its mode. Batch collects ALL members, so the
# result is an OList of the three values, in order.
let collected = now($bundle)

# any(...) yields the FIRST successful member (single winner), not a list.
# If the first member fails, any() tries the next, and so on.
let first = now(any($e1, $e2, $e3))

# race(...) yields the FIRST result to settle, whether success or failure.
# In sequential mode the first member always settles first.
# NOTE: Race does not yet cancel remaining work - in concurrent mode other
# threads run to completion but their results are discarded.
let winner = now(race($e1, $e2, $e3))

# ── Group over deferred Requests (needs a working Nix; commented) ─────────────
# Because batch() is a special form, you can write this directly:
#
#let builds = batch(
#    realise(instantiate($e1)),
#    realise(instantiate($e2)),
#    realise(instantiate($e3))
#)
#let paths = now($builds)
#
# The `lazy(batch(...))` wrapper is NO LONGER NEEDED - batch() already captures
# its arguments lazily. The above is equivalent to the old:
#
#let builds = lazy(batch(
#    realise(instantiate($e1)),
#    realise(instantiate($e2)),
#    realise(instantiate($e3))
#))
#
# autonomous(batch(...)) is the scheduler integration: the inner Requests are
# buffered, the scheduler dispatches them concurrently (up to parallelism cap),
# and the batch resolves into a list of StorePaths from the cache.
# On cache miss after flush, a hard error is returned (CacheMode::Strict).
#
#let scheduled = autonomous(batch(
#    realise(instantiate($e1)),
#    realise(instantiate($e2)),
#    realise(instantiate($e3))
#))

markdown^(
# Step-4 coordination primitives

- batch group (unforced): `$bundle`
- batch forced (collects all): $collected
- any group (first winner): `$first`
- race group (first to settle): `$winner`

A `Group` is a control value: spliced raw it renders as a marker (above), and
forced with `now(...)` it resolves per its topology mode.

**Mode semantics:**
- `batch`: collects ALL outcomes; failures become `OError` values in the list
- `all`: hard barrier - any failure aborts the entire group
- `any`: returns the first SUCCESS; tries members in order; fails only if all fail
- `race`: returns the first SETTLEMENT (Ok or Err); does not cancel losing work
)_markdown
